Reception was dealt with quickly, and although the restaurant was closed, they found some beers for us, and allowed us to use the facilities to eat food which we obtained from nearby. Rooms were good, clean and well equipped. Breakfast was great, with omelettes cooked to order as well as the usual buffet fare. We travelled rounf Myanmar and returned to this hotel 2 weeks later to the same standard of service. Can't comment on the nearby ameneties, or the area in general as we were merely 'passing through' and needed a bed for the night. Overall, a good hotel with everything you need for a short stay. title: Silver Green Hotel

title: Hotel Shwe Eain Taw
address: E Horse Race Course Rd, Yangon 11181
user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Theo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX1q9-gRFTa-cXzjc58mcRbRj__l9RydXLgOSW0ZmxRcQ0xXuRm=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This is my new favorite hotel. The prices here at the time I got here was a bargain!

You get to have free breakfast and a very large room for under $15.

Not too bad...

The only downside is the location. It is terribly far from anywhere I deem fun and exciting. It is 50 minutes away walking distance to the park. 45 minutes away from a decent gym. The market is also 20 minutes of walking.

If you are a solo traveller who loves to walk and loves affordable stays that punches above it's weight. Stay here!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP0YIweIXQ2WTpaUERafUUsjhqZ0YKEz5uIycz0&fid=0x0:0x1b5bc3fb87e20b49"],"When":"2024-1-14"},{"Name":"Steve R","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeFH6dzZjd_ZFLhXHZKibEzXEy8hWzFB4Qa7PutLe3CnO2G7yVfjd4VSabiCQwQYo5W-g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I booked the hotel for 3 of us in a family room for 3 nights. We were running the Yangon marathon (superb) and it is 2k from the start we walked home its that close.  ||||The hotel dosnt look great with ageing decor and a tired looking exterior. Thats where the negatives stop. ||||Firstly lets put this in perspctive,our room cost 63 usd (20 bucks each) including a very nice breakfast. ||||On arrival we were greeted with an orange juice and taken to our room by 3 porters lugging our bags up 4 stories to our room. We had a fantastic view (see picture), flat screen tv with sports and movies in english, newly installed air con, en suite with electric shower (reliably warm) and comfortable beds with clean sheets and towels. What else do you want. ||||The staff are so helpful bringing up water, beers, food and anything else we needed no matter what time of the day. The breakfast is great and they even remember if you like ketchip or chilli sauce and your choice of fruit the next day. The eggs are perfect!||||On the last night I sat and watched football with the local guys on a 40" TV and we had a great laugh whilst I ate my excellent 3 dollar special fried rice packed with chicken, pork, prawns...that I had no chance of finishing due to the volume.||||All in all a fantastic place which is 15 mins from airport and anything else in the city.  With taxis costing about 3 dollars to just about anywhere.  ||||This is not the ritz but is clean, authentic with great people. I would stay here again and again.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Canndy H","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeYuXGoFc9HnT35lAJ46cKDIsHY7nNIKUKz_f8yINNlqyrU48jCx-4ctPzihRKgde030w=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"The location is away from the city but transportation is not the problem as Yangon city is a TAXI city. title: Excel Palace Hotel
address: 25(D-1), New University Ave Road, Bahan Tsp., Northern Yangon, Yangon 11181
descriptions: Warmly decorated rooms with Wi-Fi in an unpretentious hotel offering a restaurant & breakfast.
complete_address: {"borough":"","street":"25(D-1), New University Ave Road, Bahan Tsp., Northern Yangon","city":"Yangon","postal_code":"11181","state":"","country":"MM"}
user_reviews: [{"Name":"Nick N","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeNj0UTN0yIrCGyJ0JhWwDODOg5QjAH0gdfB9Ji-oFl0zWFI-YVmhNAr-FGLycdpIjFmw=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"The desk staff was awesome!!  They were very helpful and spoke a good bit of English.  The upscale home turned hotel, looked tired and in need of repair.  But there was a lot of very nice woodwork all around and the hotel had \"character,\" for sure! ||||I personally enjoyed sitting out by a small balcony reading and watching the birds.  ||||They had a free breakfast in another next door restaurant which four breakfast options.  The breakfast was very good, and the waiters/waitresses were very friendly and helpful.  We had three of the four breakfast options and they were all good.||||Here was one of the meals:   Steamed Dimsum, fried noodles, chicken sausage,  sliced Honey Dew and Papaya with something on it that tastes like a perfume smells but is really good with coffee and Oolong tea.  Oh,  and some  kind of  a fish meat based hot sauce...also good.||||From the airport to the hotel we got a taxi from the taxi desk inside for 6,000 MMK but going back we found a taxi that only charged us 4,000 MMK.||||It was a nice place to stay on a budget!!  I would stay there again.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"ukairo_dash","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QcnOWm00_8Vg0_qD09-e04s-i2bb5F6bVsdwxSboR_yrT1yPvciwzMvgtJ8p5a3bvmZzg=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Stayed at the Excel Palace for 4 nights of a month long stay in Yangon. So in an apples-to-apples comparison, it is close to 3 stars. . .  but falls short in several ways. You be the judge:||The room was large and wasnt lacking for furniture, but the drapes were badly torn and the bedding had a lot of visible stains.  ||The plush headboard was likewise filthy and the pillows were very well used.||Moving on to the bathroom, the shower had plenty of hot water but 75% flowed out if the downspout, leaving the shower with rather weak pressure. The shower head was mounted below chest level. I brought these issues up with the staff on day 1, but there was no change during our time there.||Finally, the free breakfast. It was next door in a busy restaurant. There is a choice of 4 set menus with no changes allowed (it is not a buffet). Most hotels (every one we have stayed at in Yangon) have a buffet. The restaurant wouldn't even give us water, only tea or coffee (which I doubt is from filtered water). The water at the hotel is turbid (a light brown color), and I imagine that is what you get with the tea/coffee.||We brought our own bottled every morning which was not a problem.||I would give details about the number of flies in the restaurant, but suffice it to say that if you dont like flies buzzing everywhere, you might want to avoid the place.||The location (walking distance to the lake) was ok. A longer walk to other restaurants (with the exception of a Thai restaurant just across the street which was excellent).||All in all, I'd like to give it 3 stars. The house is nice. They could quickly fix most issues. But it seems the management is not of a mind to follow through.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"John C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qdx0CtChWdL4amzhVtedU6JgNzs3A9KzPS8K998c7-u-mDeTb-7WQwuTD-PPX6BcVA5wg=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Hotels in Yangon, now that Myanmar is the \"flavour of the month\", are now very expensive with the xception of the Excel Palace. It is not downtown but close to Inya Lake and the Inya Lake Hotel which is where I wanted to be close to.||It is an old private home and has no lift but spiral staircases, so be warned.||My room was large with two twin beds. All shampoos, soap etc were all supplied, as was free water every day. There is a safe in the room. The WiFi worked well.||There is also a well stocked bar fridge and the beer price was cheaper than buying outside!||The reception staff could not be more helpful...nothing was too much trouble.||The included breakfast is not in the Hotel but just around the corner in a restaurant.||The service there was a mixture of very good, when the waitresses were working our table but a bit hit and miss when it was waiters!!||Taxis are everywhere and very cheap so it is easy to get to anywhere you want to go with no problems.||Would I stay there again...you bet I would...very happily.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mike S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qf66pF81jsVXBxevYxxL5FsdlDsKAngAUpJVE-hAwai1rl8J0QnYqktKV3UGdpbmNlc_A=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"We only arrived at 4pm and left at 5am the following morning but the service and assistance we received from the front desk was outstanding. We needed a bus booked the following morning and that was no problem – they also had the taxi ready for us at 5am the following morning before we even got down to reception. The room itself was so big (but a refreshing change from some others), that it had two air conditioners. We were on the top floor – if you have an irrational fear of pigeons, maybe request a room on a lower floor, as we had a few scratching around on the roof, not enough to wake us up though.||||We didn’t get to try breakfast before we left. There are a few decent looking restaurants right near the hotel although we didn’t get a chance to try them either. The Excel Palace is in walking distance to Inya Lake and only a short drive to Shwedagon. Unless you want to be in walking distance of Sule Paya and Bogyoke Markets, I’d recommend this place purely for the service.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"kayk44","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QdGDJ6WBs5CBoNVcQAwShh25kntoFa0rN3szxhkmmJHnXagNPuSfO1BRpzbnKc5wyCe_g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"We stayed at Excel Palace Hotel for 22 days. Had a bad experience about room cleanliness.

Front Service/ 3 Stars - have to wait extra 35 min after 2 pm check-in time in order to get my room, no greeting when guests in or out. I have to greet good morning first.

Room/ 3 Stars - made a reservation with a confirmation of Premier room with king bed size in advance but they gave me twin joint bed, normally I won’t have any problem either King or twins Zipped bed however under the twin zipped bed, they placed normal sponge sheets which very hot and uncomfortable to sleep on. When I complained they said it was their standard.

Room Cleanliness/ 2 stars - a lot of previous guests hair (all type of hair) in under the floor and a lot of dust on the table. Extra pillow also very dirty, there was still on spot of stained on pillow, Look like a stained of human sperm.

When I called Front office staff and show him how bad the room was arranged, they finally switch with another but have to wait 3 more hours to be able to move to new room. I don't know why many people are giving them such high ratings. Maybe they got lucky or they have never stayed in a hotel that offers these services. The driver is always chewing on something ghastly and spit quite often, horrible. For such a good hotel has anyone seen the bed sheets, maybe one should before even sitting on it. Maybe people who are giving such good reviews are used to sleep on dirty beds. Anyway to cut the talk short, watch what you eat and don't be a fool.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Dinesh kumar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV_GuDRTv1WgjN1nG59cJbQ5XBwhgOcvyBTy3ErbwqA6oUWZWG3=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"New review 2019:

The hotel has been upgraded with the same excellent service as before. The rooms are clean and maintained well. They even have an ATM in the lobby. There is a 24hour CityMart (local supermarket) nearby. Since the hotel is on the main road, you can easily get Grab (like Uber car sharing service) and go around the city.

Do read my previous review below:

*****************************
Old review from 2017 below:

We stayed in the hotel for 3 nights in the Superior twin room and 2 nights in the Junior Suite B with Bathtub. As most of the reviews have already mentioned,  choose the rooms towards the back of the hotel (away from the road) and preferably to the right (facing east), these rooms have a better view and also you will get a glimpse of the rising sun. The hotel's buffet breakfast is great and each day they have a special local cuisine. This, in my opinion, would be a very safe way to try out the local dishes. The staff can speak English and are very friendly. The rooms are clean and we'll  maintained. The only problem is  that the doors do not appear to be sound proof and could be a problem if there are a lot of guests moving in-and-out of their rooms. TIP: There is a City Mart outlet straight down the road, about 15mins walk. There is a hospital nearby. There are some great food places in about 15mins walk.  (Note: photos are from the Junior Suite B room #403)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNTRys335Gz8GYnI6YYBqGeugAo2Gk_wDNJK7Uv&fid=0x0:0x2c8d2472717556e6"],"When":"2018-1-7"},{"Name":"Sandy’s Shine","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXd9XwYaXMx0VXxehGbmy_BXGG7o4D1R7qOLglJAXom2nLJ9IM=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Best technology in the leather industry","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ian Borja","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUNLX_Fs9Bq4tJkkoiCk_V6a2wYuYVowqo_cuP2tYcQNCXRug1DBw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Small hotel of about 20 rooms. They do have good bed sheets, nice cozy room, very clean toilet and bathroom, and their towels are nice too.

They also have a simple buffet breakfast but would surely be filling. They have the normal fried rice, noodles, veggies, fishball, mominga, congee, bread, coffee & tea, different spreads, cereal, juice and fruits.

All staff, including the owner James, are very friendly  and they will make sure you will have the best stay.

Downside is location is in a main highway, but the noise is bearable. It is located a bit far from downtown area. Cab fare though is very inexpensive in Myanmar especially if you use Grab. If you let the front desk of the hotel book your Grab ride, you will even get a.discount.

Definitely this is a value for money hotel.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"陳適恆","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL9Qa9YgyEIj_SG6Dkjal_b0smqbVY9X9C36qkb8MzTlsHDqg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is one of the best hotel I have ever stay in my life. They have budget rooms as well but the pagoda view room was worth the extra money spent. I also enjoyed the work out room! It is a great peaceful hotel in the Golden valley of Yangon. My home away from home. Love it!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Helena L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QdcKHisBXAOJmIugCgnKbcAscQkQI1t40WdQAMXk1g3ttzWj18FtKnHxNeSUm5OfHPMtQ=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I spent 4 days in Yangon and would like to recommend a stay at the Amassador Hill! You can easily grab a car to downtown with 2-3USD.   |||Staffs and the boss were super friendly and helpful!!   They helped me to call taxi to airport coz I wasn’t able to get a grab car in that morning.   Once again GRAB in Yangon is very reliable in Yangon. It's a 20 minute walk or a $1.50 taxi ride to HleDan center, a western style mall. Fuji restaurant is even closer and has great food and is safe. The breakfast is good, with traditional Myanmar food available upon request. I highly recommend the hotel, as it's quiet, clean, comfortable and affordable, all things that are hard to find in Yangon","Images":null,"When":""}]

title: Royal Ruby Hotel
address: R5MG+7FJ Royal Ruby Hotel, Yangon
descriptions: Straightforward hotel featuring a restaurant, plus complimentary breakfast & Wi-Fi.
user_reviews: [{"Name":"May Leh Khaing H","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qf66pF81jsVXBxevYxxL5FsdlDsKAngAUpJVE-hAwai1rl8J0QnYqktKV3UGdpbmNlc_A=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"My friend and I have stayed there on 28th Nov. wish I have stayed there more. |Ambient is cozy and family-like. |The hotel staff including the owner were friendly and kind to all the guests. |The room was small but they made it nice and just nice for the space they have! |Most importantly, it's clean!! |We asked for extra blanket and was provided within a short while. ||The breakfast was served at the nice area, so-called \"small garden\". I wasn't hungry that morning and was up late, so didn't try any other food except the toast bread with tea. ||If the lobby is slightly bigger, it would have been perfect. The guests of the hotel guests might need to sit and wait or meet at the lobby. ||Overall, it was a nice experience. |Will stay there again when I'm in Ygn next time.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Thant Z","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeCck1CfANpZm9bBk3PHtP97Kh9k25HZfvq9yAWlN3BaIyjSHUPEfWkhAJmuYiJsH-_6g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Good location not too far from the city center. Located in the quiet locality while not far away to access to the main road. Very attentive service with very good breakfast (mostly Asian) and the best for me is the value of money. Another point for this hotel is easy to access to the city center while you are not in the middle of roads where traffic is terrible most of the time. Really love this place.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Egil Østlid","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUV5D39QmW7t1TMpjc3BQJtkZJ7Xb4C1jRgi_eOalOOsBBCu7tm=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Good place to stay for a few days in Yangon, Myanmar","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"AlSandiego73","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QfjHmZg8gr7jpDgKhrh5KsR_Mq7L6pkVedvpKQz-f3LMiOd3OjI90CK4uLtF3wE59zZgA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I spent a total of six nights at the Royal Ruby split into two stays, so I feel pretty qualified to review this property. The most important thing to know going in is that this is a fairly small hotel. The lobby is quite compact, and even though there is a couch there usually are 2-4 people hanging out (I could never tell if they were all hotel employees or just friends). ||||For both stays I was given room #8004, right around the corner from the front desk. It might be the largest room in the hotel - there was a big, flat-screen TV, some comfortable chairs, a twin bed, and a double bed. The air conditioning was pretty strong but could be adjusted with the remote. For the first 3-4 nights there were a couple of mosquitoes that had gotten into my room somehow which made sleeping a bit difficult (I tend to attract them) in spite of the A/C being on.||||The bathroom is small but totally functional. I appreciated the modern fixtures, especially the square-shaped sink with a fairly deep basin. No problems with hot water or water pressure.||||Breakfast is served on the roof where there is an indoor eating area as well as outdoor tables. The manager, U Shwe (Mr. Gold), has done a nice job turning the outdoor space into something of a sanctuary by stringing vines and plants over the balcony so that you don't really see the busy and dusty street below. It's very green and pretty comfortable, but it's the only place to \"hang out\" and is not free from mosquitoes since it's outside.||||The choices at breakfast are quite diverse and do rotate, so if you stay for a few days you'll see different dishes. Mostly Myanmar-style food with rice, noodles (usually oily), vegetables, soup, a couple of meat dishes, etc. though there is fruit and a couple of different bread products with butter and jam. U Shwe is always at breakfast and does a great job making guests feel at home, even to the point of plating food for them and bringing it to the table. His English is excellent and he's very helpful, so if you have any questions and/or need assistance of any kind be sure to seek him out.||||The location of this hotel is a half-block off of a busy street (Yadanar Road) that doesn't have a sidewalk and isn't really walkable. There is a Chinese/Thai-style restaurant just half a block up that is a good option if you don't want to eat at the Royal Ruby. It's on the same side of the street and serves decent food. ||||There is free wi-fi at the Royal Ruby, but as is often the case in Myanmar the connection seems to go in and out randomly. I was unable to connect with my iPhone but had no problem with my laptop, and in the mornings (before 9am) and evenings (after 7pm) the connection on my laptop was pretty good.||||The only reason I stayed at this hotel was because it is close to the offices of the organization that hosted me during my stay. It's not one that I normally would choose for myself, but it was perfectly adequate for most of my needs. Since there is no fitness center I took a taxi to Real Fitness on Pale Road just west of Kabar Aye Pagoda Road in Bahan. They charge US$20 for a session during weekdays and US$30 on weekends...pretty steep, but I really needed a workout.||||If I go back to Yangon and need to be in this part of town, I most likely would choose to stay at the Sedona Hotel. If you need something a bit on the cheaper side, though, the Royal Ruby should work for your needs. My room was US$60/night (payable in cash, even though there's a MasterCard sign at the reception desk) which apparently is standard for that class of hotel in Yangon. The best thing about the Royal Ruby is U Shwe - I wouldn't even have bothered reviewing this property if he hadn't been such a great resource.||||P.S. I left a piece of luggage at the hotel while I traveled to Inle Lake and Bagan and stopped by to pick it up five days later. No problem with that.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mel G","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qf66pF81jsVXBxevYxxL5FsdlDsKAngAUpJVE-hAwai1rl8J0QnYqktKV3UGdpbmNlc_A=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"The royal Ruby is anew hotel just a year old, it has 39 rooms, the receptionist speaks workable English and the manager check every room for cleanliness everyday twice he insists and as I seem home running around checking things and training his new staff one and half hours every day it's a bit like being in hotel training school as everyone tries to help in this B and B trying to go up market. I had difficulty trying to organise flights on the Internet to Mruak U and after the receptionist used the phone a friend option a taxi driver with good English turned up and drove me to the airline office and a money changing shop to get the best rate which it was it turned out. The rooms are spotless with that Asian guesthouse eyesore to most westeners the wet bathroom. Yep when you use the shower if you can stop splashing the toilet if you stand up western shower not squat Asian wash style. I was the only non Asian in the place. They gave me a said count for travelling alone, I didn't,t ask for it. There is the mini bar and flat screen and individual air on unit that was all working as we'll as power adapter and multipoint charging station. Free wifi and about dial in speed which I think is not their limitation. Breakfast is certainly set up for Asian with the congee soup, noodles and there is always the eggs and toast to fall back on. The Asian sweetened bread is not my cup of tea so perhaps I should have stuck to the local fare but wanted to try the western option. There is a very good oriental restaurant about fifty yards away with dim sum on Sunday and some of the best and fastest food service for an experienced foodie. No pool or gym only it's own dining room but clean safe secure and cooperative. A cab ride to town is cheap the driver they organised with good English took me for the days travel for not much more than my original rip off airport connection. I suspect the owner is still a general so you can't get away from that. Oh the usual Asian hard as a rock mattress so I will have to mark down a star on that.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sai Nay Myo Htoon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWXb9H7lmSDH705hvaHsaDEPndoZrtaEHwYTeZXh2fJjmnNbnER=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"It is only good for middle class. The parking lot is small, rooms are not clean enough as it should  be and there is no Gym. There are mosquitoes in the deluxe room and actually, it is not worth to use the term deluxe.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Marissa B","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qf66pF81jsVXBxevYxxL5FsdlDsKAngAUpJVE-hAwai1rl8J0QnYqktKV3UGdpbmNlc_A=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"The royal ruby was a very pleasant home away from home during the 5 weeks that I stayed in Myanmar. Though the location was not the most convenient for tourist sites, the calm neighborhood is easily navigable, there is a grocery store nearby and the neighbors are vey helpful. The staff as well dealt with my every need, did laundry, helped with taxis and organized trips outside of Yangon for us. It was very clean and I would definitely stay again.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"swe win","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUqnSt0XIKEG3Xwbc5ax2LwOFpacfYwdS8pRF6s4roTvG_nSp5f=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Mosquitoes in delux room.. no decent training to service providers.. the staffs knocked the guest room door around 9:30 pm for daily charges without prior information …. title: Hotel Accord
address: No. 69 Damar Yone Street, Myay Ni Gone, Yangon 11111
descriptions: Simple rooms & suites in a casual hotel offering an airy restaurant & free breakfast.
user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Myo Thet Kyu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVqTMMPEWmJ_ABi8T-HDgXv57cXEFzvKmnHX-TvAVRICPeniuc=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"just checked-in. although location is good, the room is dirty. Dusts on the desks and the tables. And bedsheets got some stains. Try to call the reception but the in-room phone line is not working. The housekeeper came and changed the bedsheets. But the bedsheets he brought still gots some stains on it. After  he saw the stains on the new bedsheet he brought, he asked me if I still want the new sheet. he continued saying that all the bedsheets will be like this although they got it from the new laundry bag. I friendly asked if they used the outsourced service for laundry, he answered yes. I friendly told him may be the laundry service place is not working properly.. still the housekeeper resists that the laundry service they used is used by most of the famous hotels in town. I am not expecting the best top notch services but after tiring long trip, I want the place I paid for still offer the bare minimum services like clean bed sheets, a working phone line, and the clean tables and desks.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Anthony Policano","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWpjNo3VkwJLEQ-xqjh9_tk0PdvBE7vL9LDPnr7RNtrXramme0O=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Great hotel, great staff, great breakfast buffet (nice fruit plate for vegans), great central location next to a bustling local market, and always-on power with backup generator.

I stayed there twice, and my only complaint is that the first time my room was very small: for two people, we felt really cramped and couldn’t even walk past each other without someone jumping onto the bed to move out of the way (room 505), and one side of the bed didn’t have a table, and plugs behind the bed were difficult to access. The second time, the room (206) was at least a meter wider, had two bedside tables, and easy to reach plugs, which made all the difference! Another tiny complaint is that they offer water bottles but no easy-access to a more eco-friendly water refill station, but I asked the staff at the kitchen to help me and that always obliged (albeit with discomfort on their faces). Let’s do our part to use less single-use plastics!!

Other than that, I loved it.

TIP: there are a number of money changers nearby, but I only found one to sell my leftover MMK to for USD on departure, called WK at the bigger junction SW of the hotel.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jordi Clement","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV1SqkxobNOsWyLwPMFxQ_2731hIMK-DSX3qSmusyJBx1Xj1peTUQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"So far so good. From my opinion too much money for the value but it was acceptable for Myanmar standards.
The breakfast was very nice and the staff kind and helpful. The room could be in better conditions and maintenance but as well, ok.. The location is nice.
The annoying thing was the elevator/ascensor: there's only one for the whole hotel so get ready to wait long periods of time to use it, all the staff is using it continuously through all day, up and down and down to up.. It's always busy with workers. The costumers will need to wait.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Trip.com Member","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeCck1CfANpZm9bBk3PHtP97Kh9k25HZfvq9yAWlN3BaIyjSHUPEfWkhAJmuYiJsH-_6g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Location in the city center Near hotel has local market Nice and good staff Hotel convince","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Exploration773782","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QcHdm0oAuHtzPwzcwUtTqUfPbZXmYnyyN78cO7_Z2aHVLpBkIuu0olTbSpOuQZcPV9sYQ=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I stayed there 19 nighs. There are some good points (mostly) and a few bad ones. Fistly the staff is very friendly and supportive. There can be no complaints about them. Secondly the management acted very responsible, when I was in a health danger situation. I am very thankful to them for that. The bad points: One Aircon was not working and I was told beyond repair. I waited for a word of excuse (or even compensation) by the General Manger Mr. Smith Tin Win Aye, but that never happened. Finally i asked 2 time for an appointment, only to hear that "he is not free" "he is busy". Is that a proper way to behave by a GM ? I dont thinks so. Finally it must be mentioned that I could hear every word from the guests below my room. But total lack of sound isolation is common in Yangon.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Donna Fleur Raw","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWG_oDPIUYbMJOXtLU3sC9asIF8KV1bfiXDBSAgItIwke1D1LSh=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had originally planned to stay at the Hotel Accord for a only few days until I found more permanent accommodation since moving to Yangon. Unfortunately my search for an apartment took longer than expected, but the hotel’s wonderful staff and management have gone the extra mile to accommodate me for my unexpected longer stay. The hotel is run excellently with the utmost professionalism, while at the same time being so friendly and caring to its guests. The rooms are well furnished, clean, and modern. The hotels restaurant provides delicious meals too! Overall this place has been my home away from home- I highly recommend it!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jim L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qdx0CtChWdL4amzhVtedU6JgNzs3A9KzPS8K998c7-u-mDeTb-7WQwuTD-PPX6BcVA5wg=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I stayed at this hotel for two weeks. I paid for the two room suite but it still only cost me $70 US per night. Excellent value. It is located in a market area which might be a bit off putting for some but I loved the local interaction. Everything in the room worked and the beds are comfortable. Breakfast was included but fairly poor. Chose to eat a local stalls outside the hotel. Hotel is about 20 minutes walk from Shwedagon and you can easily get taxis. One tip use the grab app to book taxis. Works so well and you know the price when you book. Taxis are safe and very cheap. Reception was good and they do speak some English.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mallika R","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qf66pF81jsVXBxevYxxL5FsdlDsKAngAUpJVE-hAwai1rl8J0QnYqktKV3UGdpbmNlc_A=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"We stayed at the start and end of our trip and had contrasting experiences. The 5th floor room was very spacious, clean with good view while the 6th floor room was too small, smelling of cigarette (unless AC was on), facing back street of an apartment filled with garbage and lots of crows. Hotel was booked through package so cant comment on price. ||The staff was very helpful and even let us use the microwave for outside food we had got. Location is good and close to the Shwedagon pagoda and reasonable distance to Scott market.  Reception even helped us to book a taxi and lent umbrellas whenever we went out. They also allowed us to check out 2 hours later as we had an evening plane out of Yangoon.||Restaurant has minimal options, unfortunately not much local Burmese flavors and only 1 option for vegetarians. title: Wishton Hotel
address: No.365, Thitsar Road and Shwe Thitsar Street (Corner),No.13 Ward, Yangon
descriptions: Relaxed hotel featuring straightforward quarters with balconies, plus a gym, a cafe/bar & breakfast.
complete_address: {"borough":"","street":"No.365, Thitsar Road and Shwe Thitsar Street (Corner),No.13 Ward","city":"Yangon","postal_code":"","state":"","country":"MM"}
user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Ako Linn","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU81170LiobW34fSs6lQEhLyYMbtcDoKGDvyr6wzh9z0OFovXdt3w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I would be happy to write a review of Japanese hospitality in Myanmar!

Japanese hospitality, also known as "omotenashi," is known for its attention to detail, sincerity, and warmth. During my recent trip to Myanmar, I had the pleasure of experiencing this hospitality firsthand at a Japanese-owned hotel.

From the moment I arrived, I was greeted with a warm smile and a refreshing welcome drink. The staff went above and beyond to make sure that my stay was comfortable and enjoyable. They were always available to answer any questions I had and to provide recommendations for things to see and do in the area.

One of the things that stood out to me was the attention to detail. The room was immaculate, with every amenity I could possibly need, from a comfortable bed to a well-stocked minibar. The hotel also offered a range of complimentary services, including a daily breakfast.

But what really made my stay special was the warmth and sincerity of the staff. They truly seemed to care about my well-being and went out of their way to make me feel at home. Whether it was a friendly conversation in the lobby or a kind gesture like a the staff always made me feel welcome and valued.

Overall, I would highly recommend this Japanese-owned hotel to anyone visiting Myanmar. The combination of Japanese hospitality and Myanmar's natural beauty and culture made for an unforgettable experience. Thank you to the staff for making my stay so memorable!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jamie O","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qdx0CtChWdL4amzhVtedU6JgNzs3A9KzPS8K998c7-u-mDeTb-7WQwuTD-PPX6BcVA5wg=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I stayed for one month at Wishton while working at Myanmar Plaza. Every day it was a joy to come back to this clean and elegant hotel. The staff were very warm and friendly - from the porters up to the management.||||I stayed in a superior double room. The size was great. A lot of space to hang clothes as well as shelves, which meant I didn't have to live out of my suitcase.||||The bathroom was modern and efficient. The strong water-pressure and instant hot water made the shower a wonderful experience. The bath was nice and spacious as well.||||The wifi was good, being better at night for some reason. I connected my Apple TV to the flat screen in the room and had no connectivity issues. Video calls with New Zealand also ran smoothly.||||Breakfast was a highlight every day. Prepared by Japanese chefs, the numerous and varied options were always fresh and of good quality. Again, the staff were friendly and more than happy to assist, even asking me if I had any special requests. Sure enough, my bacon was waiting for me the next morning.||||The hotel has a restaurant, gym and underground parking lot. It is a quick and convenient taxi ride away from Myanmar Plaza. Nearby eating options depend on your willingness to "go local."||||All in all, I had a fantastic experience at Wishton and would happily stay there again.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Alan Chang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVAqn0TX1dB9zDcfXaCBm_KsnLYug-3tc5zISPjeWOymioUhY8ceg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"In my other home in Myanmar, the Japanese-style service and quality are very clean and reliable.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Walter Khun","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXfJu-h7YJypCZ9v22D7CGfLrEFm-rouNRXWjsqUE3YBAxOEpMT=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Great place for short-stay, long-stay with competitive corporate rate or reason discount.

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Aung lay","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXlbwcQoqQ5VAF-5SlQc7-YKHOLTC1m2HjTtnmKzLvbJbJDzWHr=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Nice view at roof top bar but small place","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Husnain Mohammad","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKcedHj3qEwc4-Cfz-iY8gtNKkGiFu2mq3PH46M3jimKcOCgg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The hotel is quite near the airport. The staff are very friendly and kind.

However, some of the rooms got cockroaches, and the electricity supply is a bit tricky. After power cut, U have to pluck out the card and insert again .

Unfortunately try the food from Restaurant is a bit average and food option is a bit limited.

Warm water is available, there is a small mall and supermarket 5-6 mins walk from the hotel.

The staff were friendly and helpful, they tried to help with our requests so I really appreciate the effort.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOjNQuQR8ZmnViOpsAO8KW1mZMbFGwixl35S2w8&fid=0x0:0x36cf8d93f2d0f702"],"When":"2024-5-25"},{"Name":"Hnin Oo Lwin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL4ANPSSXfmySADpKFs-bKqxub-sochB8Zkv_PMvRLQS86ODLI=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Before I was here, I didn't know if I wanted to stay here for more than a day. Then I ended up staying here for a full week. It doesn't look glamorous but the rooms are so comfortable to live in. The service really elevates your mood, it is top notch. They take care of you and everyone is so nice. I'm here as a local but they really take care of me well. I've been in some hotels where I'm ignored due to being a local but not here. The complimentary buffet breakfast is good. I've been in many hotels but this one has a great consistency of taste while also being on the cheaper side of hotels. Also, very convenient to live. There's no gym or swimming pools here though, that might be a problem for some. But there's a gym not five minute from here which is also surrounded by restaurants and aside a hospital.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Zue Zue K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qcacbd8SUzOZ5BFqcuH0dUXFfPFzIfRWlhBQfTV3kcVPU69oUP_k10j49o8svvEcoldiA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"The first one for the Myanmar’s location is 9miles and very quiet place and stay good options for the Korean tourists choose. The staff are helpful & extremely polite. I will recommend this hotel for their excellent service.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jeff","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocInoXXW0RswXKg-uMYrNMOu8Jb84FErwZg6IxStvgUb-Km2Ag=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Pretty nice and decent hotel. A nice authentic Korean restaurant a couple of units away and a western restaurant just next door. For the price that I paid, it’s a pretty decent hotel to lay your head to rest.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM-NoyeNpqi18TxZPDNj41rGItezcNxbmFrcrzl&fid=0x0:0x36cf8d93f2d0f702"],"When":"2018-12-14"},{"Name":"Vijay Kumar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUUE6ZUb0rjUiAs2MgMyEtSGk2byVlbFWZ3g10Bq1w_Tkf7efw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Good and clean hotel. I felt good staying with family. Hope you have the same experience.","Images":null,"When":""}]

Situated in a prime location, this hotel offers not only a convenient base for exploration but also stunning vistas of the river and the iconic Shwedagon Pagoda.

The strategic location of Hotel Grand Vista is a standout feature. Positioned in the heart of Ahlon Township, guests have easy access to key attractions, shopping centers, and cultural sites. The proximity to the river adds an extra layer of charm, providing guests with picturesque scenes and a tranquil ambiance that feels like a retreat within the city.

The highlight of this hotel is undoubtedly the panoramic views it offers. Rooms and common areas are strategically designed to showcase the beauty of the Yangon River and the majestic Shwedagon Pagoda. Witnessing the sunrise or sunset against these iconic landmarks from the comfort of your room is an experience that adds unparalleled value to your stay.

The accommodations at Hotel Grand Vista are a testament to comfort and sophistication. Well-appointed rooms with modern amenities ensure a relaxing retreat after a day of exploration. The blend of contemporary design and local influences creates a unique atmosphere that reflects the rich cultural tapestry of Myanmar.

Service at Hotel Grand Vista is characterized by warmth and efficiency. The staff's dedication to ensuring a seamless experience for guests is evident in every interaction. From the moment of check-in to personalized assistance throughout the stay, the hospitality reflects a commitment to guest satisfaction.

The on-site dining options contribute to the overall allure of the hotel. Whether indulging in local delicacies or savoring international cuisine, guests are treated to a culinary journey that caters to diverse tastes. The restaurant's ambiance, coupled with impeccable service, enhances the dining experience.

In conclusion, Hotel Grand Vista in Ahlon Township, Yangon, is a captivating blend of convenience, luxury, and awe-inspiring views. Whether you're a traveler exploring the city or a business professional seeking a comfortable retreat, this hotel exceeds expectations, providing an unforgettable stay characterized by exceptional service and breathtaking panoramas.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Aung Pyae","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLiII0Syf3nSXA5B3SZ3DHTG5mxV308k2zHkuer_eIu5EltUaE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"indoor swimming pool open till 7 pm.

the hotel rooftop have The Strip Yangon Bar.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMXSQhZk8zMlncyeCWZTzd6liOVhEgzYZUOybHB&fid=0x0:0x8dc8b7818ced9ec"],"When":"2023-10-14"},{"Name":"zarniryan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXYrQvP870QThWUf6UxSgO4wW_brQekrmeDowopRQayjAY4z3W2=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Grand Vista is located on lower Kyimyindaine St. The hotel suits for businessperson who stay for a night or something. it also has roof top bar for your recreation. title: Hotel H Valley Yangon
address: 24 Shwe Gon Taing Street 3, Yangon
descriptions: Cosy rooms & suites in a laid-back hotel offering a bar, a restaurant & a cafe, plus free breakfast.
user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Ye Linn Aung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVZoaCe4c9RPsb86zp6LF15u3dKGeMIQ9TEi8FCYnu80I2P2Nqfkg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Modern Comfort in the Heart of Yangon

Looking for contemporary style and amenities in the center of historic Yangon? Look no further than the H Valley Hotel. This modern hotel boasts sleek rooms, first-rate service, and a prime location to experience all that Yangon offers.

From the moment I walked into the lobby, I was impressed by the chic, minimalist decor. Rooms follow the same aesthetic with floor-to-ceiling windows, plush white linens, and a muted gray and teal color scheme. Touches like rainfall showers, free Wi-Fi, and city views from my room made it an urban oasis. I loved starting mornings with the lavish breakfast buffet.

But what I appreciated most was the excellent service. The friendly staff went above and beyond, arranging tours, transportation, dining reservations, and airport transfers seamlessly. Their attention to detail embodies Asian hospitality.

For visitors who crave modern amenities without sacrificing an authentic cultural experience, H Valley is a perfect home base. This polished hotel lets you indulge in 21st-century comforts while exploring one of Asia’s most mesmerizing cities.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mike E","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qf66pF81jsVXBxevYxxL5FsdlDsKAngAUpJVE-hAwai1rl8J0QnYqktKV3UGdpbmNlc_A=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Set on a side street, 10 minutes walk from Shwedagon Pagoda. Stayed here 2 nights bed and breakfast. On entering made to feel welcome by friendly smiling staff.|Lobby/Reception area fresh and clean looking.|Room of a good size, again clean. Bed comfortable, pillows nice and soft, linen bright white looking, with a fresh smell.|Bathroom a good size, clean, bath towels not so soft.|Breakfast, was fine to start the day, a small variety of choice. |Staff, very friendly, chatty and helpful, always willing to assist, nothing of any trouble.|A few minutes walk to Shwedagon Pagoda, but a taxi ride to other areas. Reception staff ordered a 'Grab' taxi for me.|Would definitely recommend this hotel and return here myself.|Great value for money","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"TJ N","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeCck1CfANpZm9bBk3PHtP97Kh9k25HZfvq9yAWlN3BaIyjSHUPEfWkhAJmuYiJsH-_6g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"The hotel is centrally located in a local vibes neighborhood within a walking distance to the Shwedagon pagoda. You can see the majestic pagoda from the 4th floor. We got upgraded to the deluxe room which was a nice gesture. The room is spacious and clean, bed and pillows were comfy, water pressure was great too. Breakfast has a good selection, the restaurant's staffs were very nice and helpful when I asked for an egg menu for my son every morning (well, all the staffs were very nice and helpful). They have some children books in English published by Myanmar Story Teller, a great gift idea for the little ones. ||Overall, my son and I had a great 4 nights stay at H Valley hotel. I'd recommend it for family travel or anyone looking for great accommodations at a reasonable price in Yangon. I wouldn't hesitate to stay again here when I'm back in Yangon next. ","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Nicolas Z","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeNj0UTN0yIrCGyJ0JhWwDODOg5QjAH0gdfB9Ji-oFl0zWFI-YVmhNAr-FGLycdpIjFmw=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"The hotel has clean and Nice room with wooden floor. I can able to see the Shwedagon Pagoda from my room window.||||Walking distance to Shwedagon and not far from most of the tourist area. 30-40min driving away from the Airport and the place is quiet at night. ||||I took only one breakfast and it is not bad. Not many choices however it is good enough for me to start of the day.||||The service is great but unfortunately there was telecom system break down to reception. So we need to go down to reception if we need the assistant.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ajith K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QfjHmZg8gr7jpDgKhrh5KsR_Mq7L6pkVedvpKQz-f3LMiOd3OjI90CK4uLtF3wE59zZgA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"The USP of this hotel is that it is centrally located and not too expensive (better booked through a travel website). It is close to the Shwedagon Pagoda, Peoples park and other landmarks. The rooms are a bit small and with the seating furniture becomes cramped. The service is good and the breakfast is reasonable. It does not have a gym or a pool, but have just opened a spa. Good for a few days stay, perhaps not for long stays.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"jaegermeister06","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qc_m0BOt0e288CC5xVhlFJeGbeLoq1HoB7h5IAKHAwOrWyFaFWxIwsJ8EDSK3zkB1-qng=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"We stayed there 3 nights. When your room is located to the direction of the lobby you will all night hear the dogs shouting and cars drive by - so you can’t sleep.||2. The staff speaks very bad English - However they are very friendly.||3. The bathroom can start to smell unexpectedly||4. It seems that the staff doesn’t know well about the city and opening hours of corresponding shops like pharmacies or money exchanges.||4. THATS THE WORST: The food which is used for breakfast is kept in the fridge and re-used again for the next day. This is especially f*cking dangerous with milk or dairy products! title: Asian Smile Hotel
address: No. 324, Thanthumar Road, Thuwanna, Yangon 11072
user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Brandon Rudd","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL3BEm67ErtBvBTnTEY_JdnDPNZmcEPQkFQ8FQpZRsN2KeORA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"An amazing place to stay if you really want to get lost in Myanmar! The staff are super kind and helpful, alongside being quite amusing at times.

They may not speak much English but they more than make up for it with service, not to mention they are very generous. A person here let me borrow some flip flops for the time I went to pagoda and helped me dress in their traditional outfit. Thanks to them I have a great experience in the country.

The location is pretty convenient too if you use the grab app, you can book a taxi and take a ride to downtown in about 10 minutes.

The room also has all the basic necessities and even come with free body wash and shampoo incase you run out as well as toothbrush.

The power may go out a few times but thats not their fault, its the countries power grid with rolling blackouts and they try to keep the power going with a generator I believe. The hot water in the shower is a little short but with how hot the country is it didn't bother me.

Hopefully they see this so thank you Asian Smile Hotel!!!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Myo Myint oo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXOmactE_SsuEBl2unndIH-zfOLgexF7ZWcsQAWzZo2mqLLULTKcA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Wide and clean room. Good place for people who would want to have some privacy without much people around. And the price is affordable as well.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Donie O","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0Qczn4VDfUM6-AtEt-6oaNazFa-i9Fy6kqPVfGIlPil6vJulEYyK8t930jZwOW4hD80mzw=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I booked a room for three nights in July 2017. The hotel is located about 45 minutes drive from airport but the taxi fare was very reasonable at 8,000 Khat. which worked out at about 6 Euro. The hotel is not near the town centre but taxis are cheap so it was not a problem. It is however near the big Pagoda which you can view after a short walk. The hotel staff are the biggest asset the hotel has because every single member of staff was very polite and friendly. The pool is outdoor and very handy for a swim. Food is varied and a freshly made omelette together with lovely fresh bread is a welcome western style breakfast. Room on second floor is preferable as music can be loud on upper floors at night. I Definitely would recommend a head and shoulder massage in this hotel as it left me feeling great by a lady who had strength which belied her small frame. The Chinese food available in the restaurant near Reception is nice and very generous portions too.This hotel is good value for money but you will have to travel further in a taxi to get a range of restaurants and shopping. A rule of thumb is about 3,000 Khat for any taxi journey to town.  The smiling and very helpful staff made our stay a nice one. Thank you Golden Butterfly Hotel.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Oof C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QfCm-MBS7Itwd4h-55xcyygsVKq1IZbUTNyg17UKkQsT2C3oSXBlQ_-pGTl8imnrFVtVw=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"The room was disgusting. Strongly urge you to go to a place like Health Blessing, a few times better","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Allan J","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QfjHmZg8gr7jpDgKhrh5KsR_Mq7L6pkVedvpKQz-f3LMiOd3OjI90CK4uLtF3wE59zZgA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"This was my 6th visit to Yangon, but my first stay at the Golden Butterfly. The hotel was chosen for its close proximity to the Shwedegon, our only reason for this visit.||The hotel is ageing, aren't we all, but it still maintains some of its old grandeur with its beautiful entrance displaying timber craftsmanship of days gone by.||||The reception was managed professionally in a friendly welcoming manner. The room allocated was airy and clean, with a very large bed, TV and room safe. The bathroom was of normal size,clean and well maintained however the old style shower bath configuration may be difficult for the aged or those with hip and back problems as the bath stands approximately 50 cm high.||||We were only at the hotel for three days/two nights and as stated earlier our sole purpose this visit was to see the Shwedegon. During OUR stay the staff were friendly and helpful, arranged taxis for us and provided us with guidance as to shopping. The restaurant staff could not have been more helpful and friendly, providing me with a large mug for my breakfast tea rather than the usual 'thimble' size cups.||||The pool area was clean and a nice place to finish one's evening with a cold beer and a glass of wine.||||Overall this is a low to medium priced hotel ideally situated for a visit to the Shwedegon. We checked-in around 3PM. Says you can check-in starting at 2PM. But when we arrived, the room wasn't quite ready yet. They were still fixing the water heater. They informed us that we'll be able to use hot water by night-time. The Side Table and Stools weren't even arranged properly when we arrived. We specifically requested the lake view room but was allocated at the 5th floor where the lake can't be seen as it's covered by trees. Still we get the view of Shwedagon Pagoda though. The room was hot, humid and a bit dusty when we checked in. Bed sheets are stained in some places but we didn't complain. What I was disgusted most by is the mold in Shower Curtains. Yuck! And hair remains in the bathtub and floor near the bed. At night, I turned on hot water and all I got was air, rusted brown water and cold water. I called them to check and they came in claiming the water is usable and is warm. It wasn't. Don't let me start with the room key card... Works 1 out of 30 tries. They came to change batteries both in the evening and the next morning. Every time we get out of the room we get locked out even though we have the key card with us. The only good thing was the tasty breakfast with a wide variety to choose from. Even for breakfast, the dining room arrangement sucked. They put two extra tables and chairs close to the buffet table and we have to tuck through these to get the food. Ugh... And they rang the doorbell at 7 AM mistakenly with the next room who were to check-out that morning. Didn't even say they were sorry for the interruption. We were given breakfast tickets but when we arrived at the dining room, no one was there to collect it so we left these tickets on the table after we were done eating. Guess what? They called us at 9AM and said it was the last call for breakfast. Good that they remind us for Breakfast, bad that they suck at who has finished eating and who have not. Overall, it seems overrated and overpriced compared to other hotels in town. Maybe they treat us locals differently from foreigners, not sure about that, as the room rates for locals and foreigners are different. But I think, for the same price, there are many hotels out there that give better service and facilities than those provided here.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOTjv-D6zKesrZz3a9TCruPYLhsrV5_JvBM9upK&fid=0x0:0xf4763ad7a8ba89c5"],"When":"2023-6-3"}]

Great location, close to area famous landmark by walking distance. Room need sound proof due to noise from street and near by park especially on morning. Also room key needed to be updated. Like old style bulk key chain back in the 80's . Great breakfast buffet and enjoy it. Staff are very attentive and helpful. Overall, very pleased with stay.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Trip.com Member","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeCck1CfANpZm9bBk3PHtP97Kh9k25HZfvq9yAWlN3BaIyjSHUPEfWkhAJmuYiJsH-_6g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"I chose to stay at this hotel based on my team’s recommendation which I booked 3 rooms but unfortunately, my experience was disappointing from the moment I arrived.I won’t comment on the door or reception staff, but I had specifically booked a deluxe non-smoking room for two people and even included this request in the additional notes on Trip.com. However, upon arrival, I was given a smoking room with a strong odor and a quilt cover stained with bright yellow urine marks. To make matters worse, the bathroom amenities were only set up for one person. When I requested additional items, the staff insisted that my booking was for a single guest. I had to show them proof from both my booking confirmation and the Trip.com request form before they only gave one additional toothbrush.Regarding non-smoking room, I again raised my concerns in the mid-afternoon, the receptionist informed me at around 8:30 PM that they could move me to another non-smoking room which I kindly declined because I dont have time to pack again as I am have other business meetings in that evening. Due to the overwhelming smoke smell and the unacceptable hygiene condition of the bedsheets, I was unable to sleep all night.As for the morning breakfast, I was once again disappointed by the poor service. I ordered an egg, but it was poorly prepared—its appearance was unappetising, almost resembling vomit. To make matters worse, when the restaurant staff brought it over, liquid from the eggs was dripping through their hands and onto the floor. It was extremely unhygienic and unacceptable.To be honest, I was deeply disappointed by the hotel’s failure to maintain even basic standards of professionalism and hygiene, let alone the expectations of a four-star establishment.I sincerely hope the hotel improves its professionalism and, most importantly, its basic hygiene. I had planned to stay again due to its convenient location near Shwedagon Pagoda, but my experience made me reconsider.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Lin Latt Htun","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXNN4TJeWej7D7EsLXEUn_ECg_6k9f8LGJh_qg7WRntgjN3I70j=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Room is clean and well organized. I would like to share my wonderful experience at Summit Park View hotel during my recent 4-night business trip. From the moment I arrived, I was met with helpful and friendly staff who made me feel welcome and valued.

One standout individual was Mr. Mark, the Executive Chef, who displayed a positive and professional attitude at all times. His culinary expertise was evident in the delicious meals I enjoyed during my stay. The variety and quality of the food exceeded my expectations, and I was thoroughly impressed.

Despite being open since 1995, the hotel is well-maintained and spotlessly clean. The attention to detail in every aspect of the hotel was commendable, creating a pleasant and comfortable atmosphere.

I must say that my overall experience at Summit Park View hotel was exceptional. The staff's dedication to customer satisfaction was evident, and I left with a lasting impression. Without a doubt, I will be returning to this hotel for future stays.

I highly recommend Summit Park View hotel to anyone in search of a memorable and comfortable stay.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Khin Aung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIfzsnbRU2Zulgxrk8OLfOuqVjTndptp32kO_H1EMWIJmEg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Good location.

The Monalisa Restaurant (Level 1) is actually excellent and reasonably priced that I ended having dinner there every night. The breakfast is not excellent but quite good.
